# 📘 EXCEPTION HANDLING

---

# 🧠 1️⃣ What is Exception?

## ✅ Definition

An **exception** is an event that **disrupts the normal flow of a program** during execution.

---

## 💡 Example

```java
int a = 10 / 0; // ArithmeticException
```

👉 Program crashes ❌

---

# 🎯 Why Exception Handling?

Without it:

* Program crashes ❌

With it:

* Graceful handling ✅
* Better user experience ✅
* Stable applications ✅

---

# 🧱 2️⃣ Exception Hierarchy (IMPORTANT)

```text id="fq16zf"
Object
   |
   |---- Throwable
           |
           |---- Exception (Checked)
           |---- RuntimeException (Unchecked)
```

---

# 🧠 3️⃣ Types of Exceptions (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)

---

## 🔹 1. Checked Exception

👉 Checked at compile-time

### Examples:

* IOException
* SQLException

---

## 🔹 2. Unchecked Exception

👉 Runtime errors

### Examples:

* ArithmeticException
* NullPointerException
* ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException

---

# 🔥 Interview Difference

| Feature  | Checked   | Unchecked |
| -------- | --------- | --------- |
| Time     | Compile   | Runtime   |
| Handling | Mandatory | Optional  |

---

# 🧰 4️⃣ try-catch (BASIC)

---

## 💻 Code

```java id="5d0ww2"
public class TryCatchDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            int a = 10 / 0;
        } catch (ArithmeticException e) {
            System.out.println("Error occurred");
        }
    }
}
```

---

# 🧠 Flow

```text id="zcc5a1"
try → exception → catch → handled
```

---

# 🧰 5️⃣ finally (IMPORTANT)

👉 Always executes (cleanup code)

---

```java id="36hqyj"
try {
    int a = 10 / 0;
} catch (Exception e) {
    System.out.println("Error");
} finally {
    System.out.println("Always runs");
}
```

---

# 🧰 6️⃣ throw vs throws (INTERVIEW FAVORITE 🔥)

---

## 🔹 throw

👉 Used to **manually throw exception**

```java id="bn1n0i"
throw new ArithmeticException("Error");
```

---

## 🔹 throws

👉 Declares exception

```java id="gdd8f6"
void test() throws IOException {
}
```

---

## 🔥 Difference

| Feature | throw         | throws           |
| ------- | ------------- | ---------------- |
| Use     | Inside method | Method signature |
| Purpose | Throw         | Declare          |

---

# 🧰 7️⃣ Custom Exception (ADVANCED 🔥)

---

## 💻 Code

```java id="cf21e7"
class MyException extends Exception {
    public MyException(String msg) {
        super(msg);
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws MyException {
        int age = 15;

        if (age < 18) {
            throw new MyException("Not eligible");
        }
    }
}
```

---

# 🧠 8️⃣ Multiple catch

```java id="vj9m2u"
try {
    int[] arr = new int[2];
    System.out.println(arr[5]);
} catch (ArithmeticException e) {
    System.out.println("Arithmetic");
} catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
    System.out.println("Index error");
}
```

---

# 🧠 9️⃣ Nested try

```java id="edgqeo"
try {
    try {
        int a = 10 / 0;
    } catch (ArithmeticException e) {
        System.out.println("Inner");
    }
} catch (Exception e) {
    System.out.println("Outer");
}
```

